  "text": "IPOPT: the IPOPT interior-point algorithm from [CITATION_1] is applied to the NLP which results from (MPOC) by reformulating all or-constraints with the aid of the smooth Kanzow-Schwartz function, see Section 3, ScholtesSC: the Scholtes-type relaxation method which is applied to a switchingconstrained reformulation (SC-MPOC) of (MPOC), see Section 4.1, ScholtesCC: the relaxation method of Scholtes is applied to a complementarityconstrained reformulation (CC-MPOC) of (MPOC), see Section 4.2, smoothedFB: the direct relaxation method from Section 5 using the smoothed FischerBurmeister function, and offsetKS: the direct relaxation method from Section 5 which exploits the offset Kanzow-Schwartz function.",
